                    <div class="faq-question">
                        Is an MBA necessary for a successful management career?
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>While an MBA is not absolutely necessary, it significantly accelerates career growth in management. It provides structured business knowledge, valuable networks, and credibility that can help you advance faster. Many senior management and C-suite positions prefer candidates with MBA degrees from reputable institutions. However, exceptional performance, industry expertise, and leadership skills can also lead to management success without an MBA.</p>
