                        How important is work experience before an MBA?
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Work experience before an MBA is highly valuable and often required by top programs. It helps you contribute meaningfully to class discussions, understand business concepts in context, and maximize your learning. Most prestigious MBA programs prefer candidates with 2-5 years of work experience. This experience also helps you identify your career goals and specialization interests more clearly, making your MBA journey more focused and effective.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
