                        Can I switch industries or functions with an MBA?
                        <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes, MBA programs are excellent platforms for career transitions. Many students use their MBA to switch industries, functions, or both. The structured curriculum provides broad business knowledge, while specializations allow you to develop expertise in new areas. Internships, projects, and networking during the program help you build credibility in your target field. However, some transitions (like non-technical to highly technical roles) may be more challenging and require additional preparation.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

